## Difference between TensorFlow and PyTorch

| Feature               | TensorFlow                      | PyTorch                      |
| --------------------- | ------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| Developer             | Google                          | Meta (Facebook)              |
| Computation Graph     | Static graph (earlier versions) | Dynamic graph                |
| Ease of Use           | Slightly more complex           | Easier and more intuitive    |
| Debugging             | Harder to debug                 | Easier to debug              |
| Research Use          | Less common in research         | Very popular in research     |
| Production Deployment | Strong production tools         | Improving production support |

---

## Simple Explanation

**TensorFlow**

* Developed by **Google**
* Widely used for **production systems and large-scale deployment**
* Provides tools like **TensorFlow Serving and TensorFlow Lite**

**PyTorch**

* Developed by **Meta (Facebook)**
* Easier to use and **very popular in research and experimentation**
* Uses **dynamic computation graphs**, which makes debugging easier.

---

## Short Interview Answer

> TensorFlow and PyTorch are both deep learning frameworks. TensorFlow is widely used for production and large-scale deployment, while PyTorch is preferred for research because it is more flexible and easier to debug due to its dynamic computation graph.

